3.Given a string s, reverse the string without reversing its individual words. Words are separated by dots(.).
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCECODE : class Solution {
    public String reverseWords(String s) { s=s.replaceAll("^\\.+|\\.+$","");
        String[] st=s.split("\\.+");
        int left=0;
        int right=st.length-1;
        while(left<right){
           String temp=st[left];
            st[left]=st[right];
            st[right]=temp;
            left++;
            right--;
        }  
        return String.join(".",st);
    }
}

Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/reverse-words-in-a-given-string5459/1
4.Given a string s consisting of lowercase English Letters. return the first non-repeating character in s. If there is no non-repeating character, return '$'.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCECODE : class Solution {
    public char nonRepeatingChar(String s) {
        int[] st=new int[26];
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
            st[s.charAt(i)-'a']++;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
            if(st[s.charAt(i)-'a']==1){return s.charAt(i);}
        }  return '$';
    }
}

