5.Given an array of strings arr[]. Return the longest common prefix among each and every strings present in the array. If there's no prefix common in all the strings, return "".
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCECODE :class Solution {
    public String longestCommonPrefix(String arr[]) {
         String p=arr[0];
         for(int i=1;i<arr.length;i++){
             while(!arr[i].startsWith(p)){
                 p=p.substring(0,p.length()-1);
             }
         } return p;
    }
}
